73. How to Access ADP's Customer Support Services 

If you are an employee whose payroll is managed by ADP, you may have questions or concerns about your account, taxes, payments or other issues related to your job. Fortunately, ADP provides excellent customer support services to help you resolve any problems quickly and efficiently. In this article, we'll show you how to access ADP's customer support services and get the help you need.

1. Start by visiting the ADP website, www.adp.com, and locate the "Help & Support" link at the top of the page. Click on this link to access ADP's Customer Service Support Center.

2. Once you enter the support center, you will have access to a wide range of self-service resources that can help you resolve common issues such as resetting your password, checking your pay stubs, or downloading your W-2 forms. You can also search the knowledge base, download user guides, and watch product demos to learn how to use ADP services effectively.

3. If you cannot find the information you need on the self-help portal, you can contact an ADP customer support agent by phone, email or chat. To contact customer support by phone, call the toll-free number that is specific to your region, which is available on the ADP website. Note that depending on your location and the type of issue you have, phone support is only available during certain hours.

4. To email customer support, fill out the online form available on the ADP website. Be sure to provide as much detail as possible about your issue, such as your account number, the nature of the problem, and the steps you have already taken to resolve it. An ADP representative should respond to your email within 24-48 hours.

5. If you prefer to chat with a customer support representative, you can access the chat function on the ADP website during business hours. This option is helpful for immediate questions or issues that do not require deep investigation. 

6. Always remember to have your ADP account number or employee identification number (EIN) handy when contacting customer support, as this information will help the agent quickly access your account and resolve any issues.

By following these steps, you should be able to access ADP's Customer Support Center and get the help you need quickly and efficiently. Remember that ADP is committed to providing excellent customer service and support to help you manage your payroll and benefits with ease and confidence.